Wydrop
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:the commonest forms of the many variants in pronunciation and spelling of early Anglicisations of Wairarapa, mainly with Maori /r/ perceived as English [d], an unstressed /a/ as [ ], and the -a final not heard
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: The NZ Journal 1841-1845 record: Wydirup (once), Wyderop (8 times) Wairarapa (twice)
